@NODE Bedienung

@{b}Usage and ergonomics@{ub}

À High-speed rendering
À Easy, uniform und fast usage of the whole program
À Asynchronouss und nonmodale windows
À Interactive realtime display
À Intuitive placement of the camera in realtime
À Fast access to all important functions over symbols
À Fast working with shortcuts
À Exact working with parameter input over keyboard or mouse
À Amiga styleguide conform user interface
À Selfexplaning functions
À Self configurable menus
@ENDNODE

@NODE Oberflõche

@{b}Graphical User Interface@{ub}

À Free position for all symbols
À Layout freely configurabl
À Display selectable between outline, draft, side, 3D or
  combinations of all four displays
À Processing of the objects in all sights
À Resolutions freely selectable
À Editor runs on the workbench
À Help function
À Several reduced display modes for fast working
@ENDNODE

@NODE Zahlen

@{b}Numbers@{ub}

À High internal computing precision
À Integrated parser for mathematical expressions like 
  +, Sin, Abs etc.
À True to scale constructing
@ENDNODE

@NODE Objekte

@{b}Objects@{ub}

À Infinite amount of objects applicable
À Thirteen different, variable basic objects
À Five different , variable polygons
À Five different special objects
À Fractals for the formation of mountain landscapes
À Unlimited amount of polygon objects, which are produced
  through drilling, pushing or rolling of a contour
  or through joining of several contours
À Rounding of edges
À Smoothing of objects with Phong-method
À Hierarchical system for the simple and efficient 
  administration of objects
@ENDNODE

@NODE Polygon

@{b}Polygon@{ub}

À Infinite many three-dimensional polygons
À Four different interpolation modes (Linear, Akima,
  B-Spline und Kubisch)
À Moving, turning, scaling of base points
À Base points can be imported from an external file
@ENDNODE

@NODE Punkte

@{b}Points, edges and plains@{ub}

À Elements changeable as you like
À Points, edages and plains can be moved, turned, scaled,
  deleted etc.
À Magnetism-function for the interactive forming of
  surfaces
À Summing up of marked elements to new object
À Import from external files
À Interactive Input in realtime and manipulation
@ENDNODE

@NODE Funktionen

@{b}Functions and tools@{ub}

À Turning, moving, scaling and sizing in realtime
À Clipboard for the comfortable data transfer between
À different documents
À Intelligent functions notice wrong inputs and support
  the user with suggestions
À Boolean operations
À Mirroring, wrapping, ordering, centering, shaping, forming
  random, optimizing, joining, smoothing and much more
@ENDNODE

@NODE Material

@{b}Materials and textures@{ub}

À Extensive, expandable matirial archive with glass, wood,
  plastic and metal etc.
À Colour, transparency, splendor, reflection and refraction
  freely definable
À Textures for realistic 3-dimensional uneveness
À Input alternatively in RGB- or HSV-System
À Plain, cylindric and spherical projection
À Colour-, transparency-, mirror-, relief-, splendor- and
  fluorescent textures
À tile textures
À Direct usage of IFF-pictures in all resolutions
  and colour depths 
À Textures can be placed interactive in realtime on the
  objects
@ENDNODE

@NODE Licht

@{b}Lighteffects@{ub}

À As many colored sources of light as you like
À Divergent und parallel light
À Shadowing
À Fllodlights
À Fog
À Sunlight (color and direction according to time of day, date and
  geographical width)
À Altogether 18 different modes of light sources
@ENDNODE

@NODE Rechnen

@{b}Rendering of pictures@{ub}

À Six different methods of visualising, from wire frame over
  scanline up to raytracing
À Different levels of quality
À Separate raytracer for best usage of memory and multitasking
À Adaptive, optimized raytracer through combination with
  scanline-algorithm
À Scanline-algorithm can display reflections of ground and
  heaven
À Complex and fast algorithms
À Qualitatively high-grade antialiasing
À Calculations in all available screenmodes (AA, ECS)
À Support of the graphic boards Retina, Merlin, Picasso and
  all EGS-boards (Piccolo, Domino, Rainbow, GVP Spectrum,
  GVP EGS-110/24, IV24, Visiona, Videolayer etc.)
À Other graphic boards accessable over library
À Output on harddisk with flexible resolutions and 16 Million
  colours possible
À Usage background and foreground picture
@ENDNODE

@NODE Animation

@{b}Animation@{ub} (only Professional-version)


À Keyframe-animation for bodies, sources of light and camera through
  interactive definition of the bases (Keyframes for position, size,
  situation, material and texture) in realtime.
À Path-animation for objects through attributing of polygons
À Real hierarchy-animation
À Timestrip for graphical controlling of the animation
À Time control for exact temporal editing of animations
À Genuine accelerating, braking as well as complex speed-functions
  applicable
À Selectable spatial and temporal interpolation modes (jump, linear,
  B-spline, akima, cubical)
À Object -, camera -, material -, texture -, light - and sun - 
  animation
À many specialefects
À Animation of background, foreground, floor, heavens etc.
À Easiest usage through functions like photograph, start, stop, 
  fast forward and rewind etc.
À Preview-function (animation can be played from harddisk or
  memory in realtime)
@ENDNODE

@NODE Format

@{b}Fileformat und Extensions@{ub}

À Powerful and documented IFF-Format 
À Converter CASTILLIAN reads and writes the formats 
  Cinema4D, Fastray, Imagine, Refelctions, Turbo Silver,
  Videoscape, Sculpt, Pagerender and DXF
À Program functionality can be expanded through documented
  interface
@ENDNODE


@NODE System

@{b}System requirements@{ub}

Following are the minimum requirements for running Cinema4D.
Note that this is really the @{i}MINIMUM@{ui}! When you are
doing raytracing especially with animations think of this:
THE MORE THE BETTER!

À Amiga-computer
  A500,A600,A1000,A1200,A2000,A2500,A3000,A4000,A3000T,A4000T
À Harddisk
À 2 MByte memory (Professional: 3 MByte)
À WB 2.0 and Kickstart 2.04 or higher
@ENDNODE


